WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.938 --> 00:00:06.039
Jerry:
Uhh. I'm so nervous!

2
00:00:06.073 --> 00:00:07.876
It's been so long. no one
even makes fun of me

3
00:00:07.909 --> 00:00:09.409
for being unemployed
anymore.

4
00:00:09.443 --> 00:00:11.913
Aw. We can make fun of you
if you want. sweetie.

5
00:00:11.946 --> 00:00:13.915
You could also
take one of these.

6
00:00:13.948 --> 00:00:15.550
It's a worry worm.

7
00:00:15.583 --> 00:00:17.785
It eats your worries
and dies out in a couple hours.

8
00:00:17.819 --> 00:00:20.053
I'm on one right now.
Super chill.

9
00:00:20.087 --> 00:00:21.789
I'm not taking
breakfast drugs!

10
00:00:21.823 --> 00:00:23.156
We doing
breakfast drugs?

11
00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:24.893
I'm just dropping
Morty off. Deal me in.

12
00:00:24.926 --> 00:00:26.460
Nobody's dealer-ing
anyone.

13
00:00:26.493 --> 00:00:29.196
Seriously. guys. this
interview is important to me!

14
00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:30.932
Wow! Good luck. Dad!

15
00:00:30.965 --> 00:00:32.767
Didn't -- Didn't realize
you were still trying.

16
00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:34.234
Yeah. Why?

17
00:00:34.268 --> 00:00:35.737
No one's on your ass
to contribute a thing.

18
00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:37.137
Ah. if you're trying to
neg me into taking a worm.

19
00:00:37.170 --> 00:00:38.338
you've succeeded.

20
00:00:38.372 --> 00:00:41.074
Negging works.
[ Gulps ]

21
00:00:41.108 --> 00:00:43.076
See you all in a week!
Mnh.

22
00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:45.078
I'm so excited!

23
00:00:45.112 --> 00:00:47.180
Guh-uh. this is what it feels
like to have friends?

24
00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:49.584
Wouldn't know.
Pick you up on Sunday?

25
00:00:49.617 --> 00:00:51.151
See you then!

26
00:00:52.620 --> 00:00:54.789
-Snowball!
-Morty!

27
00:00:54.822 --> 00:00:56.089
-[ Panting ]
-[ Laughs ]

28
00:00:56.123 --> 00:00:58.292
Oh. my God!
I missed you so much!

29
00:00:58.325 --> 00:01:00.460
Me too. Morty. Me too.

30
00:01:00.494 --> 00:01:01.596
[ Laughs ]

31
00:01:01.629 --> 00:01:10.505
♪♪

32
00:01:10.538 --> 00:01:18.846
♪♪

33
00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:26.988
♪♪

34
00:01:27.021 --> 00:01:31.759
♪♪

35
00:01:33.561 --> 00:01:35.329
[ Shutter clicking ]

36
00:01:35.362 --> 00:01:37.464
I...was there
when that happened.

37
00:01:37.497 --> 00:01:39.132
Really cool!

38
00:01:39.166 --> 00:01:41.536
Whoa! They got
a monorail. too?!

39
00:01:41.569 --> 00:01:43.871
Proud of my dog.
He built this place. you know.

40
00:01:43.905 --> 00:01:45.138
UGG! Glugg UGG!

41
00:01:45.172 --> 00:01:46.406
Agh! Shit!
What the fuck?

42
00:01:46.440 --> 00:01:48.509
Paul! Come! Up!
Don't mess with him.

43
00:01:48.543 --> 00:01:50.377
We don't know
if he's had his shots.

44
00:01:50.410 --> 00:01:54.015
Snowball: Morty.
Oh. I see you've met a mup.

45
00:01:54.048 --> 00:01:55.550
No big deal.

46
00:01:55.583 --> 00:01:58.352
Just humanoid creatures
we bred to be pets.

47
00:01:58.385 --> 00:02:01.522
Hopefully that doesn't. heh.
freak you out too much.

48
00:02:01.556 --> 00:02:03.925
Oh. Nope.
I've seen a lot of stuff.

49
00:02:03.958 --> 00:02:06.159
Good. because
it would be weird

50
00:02:06.193 --> 00:02:08.161
if <i>you</i> were
offended by it. heh.

51
00:02:08.195 --> 00:02:09.329
since you had pets first.

52
00:02:09.363 --> 00:02:11.231
[ Gasps ]
[ Sniffing ]

53
00:02:11.264 --> 00:02:14.167
Ugh! Is there anything else
we could visit or talk about?

54
00:02:14.201 --> 00:02:16.303
Yes. Good. Good.
Of course.

55
00:02:16.336 --> 00:02:18.539
BooBoo. push
the Sniff Conference.

56
00:02:18.573 --> 00:02:21.909
I've got a lot to show
my old friend.

57
00:02:21.943 --> 00:02:24.545
That's the college
of New Dog City.

58
00:02:24.579 --> 00:02:27.548
And there is our
mech-suit warehouse.

59
00:02:27.582 --> 00:02:30.051
We've updated
your grandpa's designs.

60
00:02:30.084 --> 00:02:31.619
Cool!

61
00:02:31.653 --> 00:02:34.589
I know you're probably
distracted by the mups.

62
00:02:34.622 --> 00:02:38.258
Sadly. they're all
I can see now.

63
00:02:38.291 --> 00:02:40.928
Okay. m-maybe we should
just chill at your place.

64
00:02:40.962 --> 00:02:43.831
You know?
Ch-Chill? Hang?

65
00:02:43.865 --> 00:02:45.399
[ Beeping ]

66
00:02:50.538 --> 00:02:51.471
Water bowl. sir?

67
00:02:51.506 --> 00:02:53.340
It is our finest
hose water.

68
00:02:53.373 --> 00:02:55.342
Ohh! It's shaped
like a little dog bowl.

69
00:02:55.375 --> 00:02:57.045
Tha-- Hey.
That's -- That's fun.

70
00:02:57.078 --> 00:02:58.613
Snowball:
Yes. this is good.

71
00:02:58.646 --> 00:03:02.215
We will hang by the pool
and reminisce about old times.

72
00:03:02.249 --> 00:03:03.618
No politics. [ Chuckles ]

73
00:03:03.651 --> 00:03:05.086
[ Mancors screeching ]
We got company!

74
00:03:05.119 --> 00:03:06.154
God damn it!

75
00:03:06.186 --> 00:03:07.722
-Haaaa!
-Take. take!

76
00:03:07.755 --> 00:03:09.090
Jesus Christ!

77
00:03:09.123 --> 00:03:10.591
-Take. take. take!
-Take. take. take!

78
00:03:10.625 --> 00:03:12.225
[ Morty screams ]

79
00:03:12.259 --> 00:03:14.696
You said we could
keep them out!

80
00:03:14.729 --> 00:03:15.930
We're trying. sir!

81
00:03:15.963 --> 00:03:17.632
The Mancors.
they're adapting!

82
00:03:17.665 --> 00:03:21.135
So we adapt <i>harder.</i>
General.

83
00:03:21.169 --> 00:03:23.938
You're making my friend
uncomfortable.

84
00:03:23.971 --> 00:03:25.606
Okay. Morty...

85
00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:27.240
I think you're getting
the wrong impression.

86
00:03:27.274 --> 00:03:29.242
You're seeing a lot
of physical deformity

87
00:03:29.276 --> 00:03:30.778
and selective breeding.

88
00:03:30.812 --> 00:03:33.346
and your mind is going
to all kinds of places.

89
00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:36.117
I mean. it's more that this
wasn't quite the vacation I --

90
00:03:36.150 --> 00:03:38.853
Titus. take Morty
to the mup facility. mm?

91
00:03:38.886 --> 00:03:40.988
Show him
how loved they are.

92
00:03:41.022 --> 00:03:42.322
Hey. buddy!

93
00:03:42.355 --> 00:03:44.291
Okay. Y-You don't
have to crouch.

94
00:03:44.324 --> 00:03:47.128
Wow. and it says here
under Other Experience:

95
00:03:47.161 --> 00:03:48.830
"jumped dimensions."

96
00:03:48.863 --> 00:03:50.263
What was <i>that</i> like?

97
00:03:50.297 --> 00:03:51.999
Well. you see
some things. Bob.

98
00:03:52.033 --> 00:03:53.534
but at the end
of the day.

99
00:03:53.568 --> 00:03:56.236
you realize we're all
pretty much the same.

100
00:03:57.972 --> 00:04:00.808
That's the kind of experience
I want to bring to the team.

101
00:04:00.842 --> 00:04:02.143
Incredible.

102
00:04:02.176 --> 00:04:03.443
So can I ask?

103
00:04:03.477 --> 00:04:05.646
Any big fish you're
trying to take down?

104
00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:08.950
Well. Jerry. I don't normally
talk clients during interviews.

105
00:04:08.983 --> 00:04:13.286
but. God. I'm just loving
this laid-back attitude!

106
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:15.223
Nipslip Vodka.

107
00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:16.791
If we can convince them
to hire us.

108
00:04:16.824 --> 00:04:18.693
we'd double our revenue.

109
00:04:18.726 --> 00:04:19.994
Ahh.

110
00:04:20.027 --> 00:04:21.294
I mean.
it's right there. Bob.

111
00:04:21.328 --> 00:04:22.830
It's screaming at ya.

112
00:04:22.864 --> 00:04:25.332
What? I-I-I don't see it.

113
00:04:26.033 --> 00:04:28.002
<i>Drink.</i>

114
00:04:28.035 --> 00:04:30.538
Yes. Yes! I love it!

115
00:04:30.571 --> 00:04:33.875
I love it!
So simple. So great!

116
00:04:33.908 --> 00:04:35.143
Mm. These things
come to me.

117
00:04:35.176 --> 00:04:36.409
Hey. You free tonight?

118
00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:38.146
We're having dinner
with their CEO.

119
00:04:38.179 --> 00:04:39.814
They need to
hear this. Jerry.

120
00:04:39.847 --> 00:04:43.518
and they need to hear it from
someone as confident as you.

121
00:04:43.551 --> 00:04:48.623
♪ It's Friday. Friday.
gotta get down on Friday ♪

122
00:04:51.058 --> 00:04:53.360
-Honey. I'm home.
-Jerry?

123
00:04:53.393 --> 00:04:56.329
Prospects are good. Meeting
the client for dinner.

124
00:04:56.363 --> 00:04:58.166
Oh. Uh. that's great.

125
00:04:58.199 --> 00:04:59.867
Why did you park
on the lawn?

126
00:04:59.901 --> 00:05:02.136
Jesus. How many
of these did you take?

127
00:05:02.170 --> 00:05:05.206
The first worm helped.
so I took a couple
more. No biggie.

128
00:05:05.239 --> 00:05:07.074
What's up?
Jerry O.D. on worms?

129
00:05:07.108 --> 00:05:08.441
I told him
to take <i>one!</i>

130
00:05:08.475 --> 00:05:10.443
[Burps] Holy shit!

131
00:05:11.946 --> 00:05:13.346
Jerry.
you are <i>teeming!</i>

132
00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:15.183
I-I guess you had
enough anxiety

133
00:05:15.216 --> 00:05:16.584
to fuel a worm
breeding frenzy.

134
00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:18.119
That's a <i>bad</i> thing.
right?

135
00:05:18.152 --> 00:05:19.720
It's a <i>new</i> thing.
I-I gotta admit.

136
00:05:19.754 --> 00:05:21.222
I don't know much
about the worm business.

137
00:05:21.255 --> 00:05:23.224
I'm sure my worm
dealer has a fix.

138
00:05:23.257 --> 00:05:25.960
J-Man's gonna pass
on all this.

139
00:05:25.993 --> 00:05:27.360
Honey.
you're teeming!

140
00:05:27.394 --> 00:05:29.997
Alright. But let's
wrap this quick.

141
00:05:30.031 --> 00:05:32.066
Big night ahead.

142
00:05:32.099 --> 00:05:33.701
No more
giving Jerry drugs.

143
00:05:33.734 --> 00:05:35.368
Loud and clear.

144
00:05:36.469 --> 00:05:38.239
Titus: You like that?

145
00:05:38.272 --> 00:05:40.107
We call it
a mup-a-cino!

146
00:05:40.141 --> 00:05:42.243
Mmm! Creamy!

147
00:05:42.276 --> 00:05:45.378
Biscuit. this is Emperor
Snowball's "Morty."

148
00:05:45.412 --> 00:05:46.814
As you can see.
Morty.

149
00:05:46.848 --> 00:05:48.783
it's all totally fine.

150
00:05:48.816 --> 00:05:50.483
I'm kind of getting
the impression

151
00:05:50.518 --> 00:05:52.385
that you're all sort of
ashamed of this stuff.

152
00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:54.255
Ashamed?
He seems
unconvinced.

153
00:05:54.288 --> 00:05:55.990
I'll play the video.

154
00:05:56.023 --> 00:05:58.259
Dog spokesperson: <i>And thanks</i>
<i>to new breakthroughs</i>

155
00:05:58.292 --> 00:05:59.927
<i>in cruelty-free Mup technology.</i>

156
00:05:59.961 --> 00:06:02.330
<i>you can further customize</i>
<i>your new best friend</i>

157
00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:04.966
<i>with our drag-and-drop display.</i>

158
00:06:04.999 --> 00:06:06.267
[ Mup screams ]

159
00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:07.802
<i>Hahaha!</i>
<i>And the mups like it!</i>

160
00:06:07.835 --> 00:06:10.470
<i>Non-genetic modifications</i>
<i>can also be made</i>

161
00:06:10.504 --> 00:06:12.139
<i>once your mup is born.</i>

162
00:06:12.173 --> 00:06:13.708
<i>and once the stitch is healed.</i>

163
00:06:13.741 --> 00:06:16.944
<i>your new friend is ready</i>
<i>to join the family.</i>

164
00:06:16.978 --> 00:06:18.411
<i>Super normal!</i>

165
00:06:18.445 --> 00:06:20.982
<i>And if</i> you <i>think it's weird.</i>
you're <i>weird.</i>

166
00:06:21.015 --> 00:06:22.783
[ Baby mup cries ]

167
00:06:24.685 --> 00:06:26.419
Brought you
a friiiend!

168
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:27.655
[ Coughing ]

169
00:06:27.688 --> 00:06:29.624
That's a <i>happy</i>
wheeze!

170
00:06:29.657 --> 00:06:32.293
Titus: Aww. He thinks
they're <i>inside</i> the TV.

171
00:06:32.326 --> 00:06:34.528
Play him
the video again!

172
00:06:34.562 --> 00:06:36.764
Morty?
Oh. Hey -- Hey. pal.

173
00:06:36.797 --> 00:06:38.266
Glad I caught you.
actually.

174
00:06:38.299 --> 00:06:39.667
I-I'm just
gonna take off.

175
00:06:39.700 --> 00:06:41.769
Got some homework
I forgot about. Uh...

176
00:06:41.802 --> 00:06:44.305
-Great seeing you. though.
-Right.

177
00:06:44.338 --> 00:06:45.973
So you're going to
cancel me?

178
00:06:46.007 --> 00:06:47.074
What? No.

179
00:06:47.108 --> 00:06:48.676
So you're <i>not</i> gonna run

180
00:06:48.709 --> 00:06:50.344
and tell your grandfather
I'm doing eugenics?

181
00:06:50.378 --> 00:06:52.613
You're projecting so much
specific shit onto me!

182
00:06:52.647 --> 00:06:54.181
You think I'm racist.

183
00:06:54.215 --> 00:06:56.684
Listen. I came here
as your friend.

184
00:06:56.717 --> 00:06:58.753
That's how
I wanna leave.

185
00:06:58.786 --> 00:07:01.454
Okay. Just had
a lot planned.

186
00:07:01.488 --> 00:07:03.925
Didn't even get to see
our giant sprinkler.

187
00:07:03.958 --> 00:07:05.993
Next time. O-Okay?

188
00:07:06.027 --> 00:07:07.561
Okay...

189
00:07:11.498 --> 00:07:12.600
[ Door closes ]

190
00:07:12.633 --> 00:07:14.201
[ Panting softly ]

191
00:07:16.203 --> 00:07:18.339
Please don't try to kill me.
Please don't try to kill me.

192
00:07:18.372 --> 00:07:19.607
Please don't try
to kill me.

193
00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:21.342
[ Crash ]
Titus: Oh. shit!

194
00:07:21.375 --> 00:07:23.010
[ Tires screech ]
God damn it!

195
00:07:23.044 --> 00:07:25.680
-Oh. God!
-On the ground! Down! Down!

196
00:07:25.713 --> 00:07:28.649
♪♪

197
00:07:28.683 --> 00:07:30.351
[ Tires screech ]
[ Horn honks ]

198
00:07:30.384 --> 00:07:32.920
Driver: Get out of the road.
you dumb mup!

199
00:07:32.954 --> 00:07:34.487
Oh...no...

200
00:07:34.522 --> 00:07:35.990
[ Mups snarling ]

201
00:07:36.023 --> 00:07:37.992
[Mancors shrieking]

202
00:07:38.025 --> 00:07:39.360
♪♪

203
00:07:39.393 --> 00:07:40.528
[ Snarling ]

204
00:07:40.561 --> 00:07:42.029
Oh. fuck me!

205
00:07:42.063 --> 00:07:43.664
-Take. take. take. take!
-Take. take. take. take!

206
00:07:43.698 --> 00:07:46.734
Wait! Maybe they can't
see us if we don't move!

207
00:07:46.767 --> 00:07:49.704
Never mind! Run!
[ Whimpers ]

208
00:07:49.737 --> 00:07:52.340
[ Sniffing ]
Take-take?

209
00:07:52.373 --> 00:07:56.210
Ugh. Please don't take me
to join some kind of rebellion.

210
00:07:56.243 --> 00:07:58.913
Yah. Take-take.

211
00:07:58.946 --> 00:08:01.816
[ Mancors shrieking ]
Aww. man!

212
00:08:05.753 --> 00:08:08.189
Uh. hello? Sweet Marie?

213
00:08:08.222 --> 00:08:10.858
[ Lizard growls and screeches ]

214
00:08:10.891 --> 00:08:12.560
Brought the
whole family. huh?

215
00:08:12.593 --> 00:08:13.761
We're cool.

216
00:08:13.794 --> 00:08:16.597
Yeah. we're...
ice cold.

217
00:08:17.932 --> 00:08:20.267
As you can see.
my idiot kinda-husband

218
00:08:20.301 --> 00:08:21.702
took too many
Flaxar worms.

219
00:08:21.736 --> 00:08:23.404
and they are now
reproducing inside him.

220
00:08:23.437 --> 00:08:25.773
Cha-ching!
You want to go 60/40?

221
00:08:25.806 --> 00:08:27.908
We're trying to fix him. not
get into the worm business.

222
00:08:27.942 --> 00:08:29.877
Well. hold on.
Who's getting that 60?

223
00:08:29.910 --> 00:08:32.847
Dad. we are not
letting this woman
harvest Jerry for worms!

224
00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:36.650
Marie? You texted "Come in"
and then a gun emoji?

225
00:08:37.451 --> 00:08:38.853
Space Beth: Yah!

226
00:08:38.886 --> 00:08:41.055
[ All grunting ]

227
00:08:41.088 --> 00:08:42.857
[ Sweet Marie screams ]

228
00:08:42.890 --> 00:08:45.826
God damn it. Dad! Good
dealers don't grow on trees!

229
00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:47.328
Infinite multiverse.
sweetie.

230
00:08:47.361 --> 00:08:49.096
There <i>are</i> trees
that do that.

231
00:08:49.130 --> 00:08:50.898
[ All grunting ]

232
00:08:50.931 --> 00:08:53.434
♪♪

233
00:08:53.467 --> 00:08:55.036
[ Screeching ]

234
00:08:57.171 --> 00:08:58.672
Beth: Shit. Jerry!

235
00:08:58.706 --> 00:09:00.274
Hmm. We better
find him fast.

236
00:09:00.307 --> 00:09:02.710
If the worms hit a tipping
point on Jerry's anxiety.

237
00:09:02.743 --> 00:09:04.979
they'll start using him to
feed on other people's worry.

238
00:09:05.012 --> 00:09:07.782
You mean...
He's going to feed on
creating discomfort.

239
00:09:07.815 --> 00:09:10.151
Oh. boy.
He'll be great at it.

240
00:09:11.485 --> 00:09:12.787
Jerry's tracker
disappeared here.

241
00:09:12.820 --> 00:09:14.321
The worms
must have eaten it.

242
00:09:14.355 --> 00:09:15.990
Those things impress me
more and more by the minute.

243
00:09:16.023 --> 00:09:18.426
Rick: They're a gold mine.
Hold on.

244
00:09:18.459 --> 00:09:19.794
[ Grunts ]

245
00:09:19.827 --> 00:09:21.595
<i>Surprise improv</i>
<i>on the subway!</i>

246
00:09:21.629 --> 00:09:23.464
<i>Hey. want to jump in. sir?</i>

247
00:09:23.497 --> 00:09:25.466
